        "header": "3Methodology",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.10268/2605.10268v1/x5.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Framework of MemReread.MemReread adopts the streaming memorization paradigm. Upon detecting an information deficit within the terminal memory, it decomposes the initial question, then executes targeted rereading based on the generated sub-questions, and subsequently integrates the derived sub-answers back into the terminal memory.",
                "position": 556
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.10268/2605.10268v1/x6.png",
                "caption": "Figure 5:Overall of the Advantage Design.The advantage calculation comprises two components. For process supervision, we adopt the memory part of ReMemR1’s state rewards. For outcome supervision, we employ a Rereading-Adaptive Outcome Advantage calculation.",
